  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      After resection of lymph node positive breast cancer, the injection duration and timing of
      Granulocyte-colony stimulating factor (G-CSF) could affect the neutropenia with TAC
      (Taxotere, Adriamycin, cyclophosphamide) chemotherapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The duration and the injection timing of G-CSF are effective in the prevention of
      neutropenia, incidence of infection and non hematologic toxicity. With the TAC chemotherapy
      after resection of breast cancer, the G-CSF early injection versus late injection could
      change the frequency of neutropenia.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
